HEADWORD: Semimonthly
<hw>Sem`i*month"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Coming or made
twice in a month; <as>as, <ex>semimonthly</ex> magazine; a
<ex>semimonthly</ex> payment.</as></def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>Something done or made every half month; esp., a semimonthly
periodical.</def></def2> -- <def2><pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a semimonthly
manner; at intervals of half a month.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semimute</ent>⟦br⟧
